ery runs out. Corded trimmers are ideal for those who desire continuous sessions and will only use them in one place. They're ideal for people who travel and prefer to bring their trimmers with them. Consider it a trimmer that you can plugin and keep in your bathroom. Build Quality Regardless of what you're buying, this is a critical consideration. It is considerably more critical in the case of men's trimmers. An expensive trimmer may have poor build quality, but a low-cost one may have excellent build quality. You need to locate a high-quality product that does not come at an exorbitant price. These are the aspects to consider, from a solid build quality (perhaps stainless steel body) to a design with a tight grip. Trimmer Level Setting A crucial factor is the trimmer-level adjustments. The beard is trimmed with a trimmer to the appropriate level. Therefore, a single measure is insufficient. The trimmer's level adjustments range from 1 mm (a clean shaved) to 10 mm (the longest). Please don't go for a shaver without a length adjustment; be certain it has the correct length option. Types of Blades Another most common options in this area are blades made from stainless steel. Trimmers with stainless steel blades last a prolonged time and don't corrode. On the other hand, a carbon steel blade is prone to corrosion yet provides accurate trimming. To prevent corrosion, search for titanium plating or, even preferably, a trimmer containing titanium blades. These are the finest resilient and won't tarnish or corrode. Finally, we have ceramic blades, which provide a sharp reaction but are fragile and may break. Battery Runtime Battery charge and runtime are linked, as previously stated. When shopping, seek a shaver having a minimum battery runtime of 65 to 90 minutes. It's comparable to owning a phone that needs to be constantly charged to have a wireless trimmer with a battery life of only 5 or 10 minutes. Trimmers with a runtime of 1 to 1.5 hours are available on the market. Anything less will not suffice. Charging Time Most customers will purchase trimmers that can be used in both corded and cordless modes. As a result, selecting a device that charges quickly is critical. A four to six hours charge period is required for a run time of anywhere between 60 and 90 minutes. Look for fast charging options that allow you to trim quickly after only 5 or 10 minutes of charging. Budget Trimmers are available in various price ranges, but getting the perfect one is ideal. Whether you have a limited budget or can stretch it, choose one that checks most boxes and does not skimp on build quality or functionality. Budget trimmers frequently make compromises in order to provide specific features, so be cautious to weigh the benefits and drawbacks. Brand Warranty Please keep in mind that warranty isn't the most important factor to consider. Most reputable brands will provide a multi-year guarantee as well as excellent after-sales service. In an ideal world, you should weigh all of these factors equally. A decent trimmer will last for a long time. Let us see some of the best trimmers for men- 1. Philips QT4001/15 Beard Trimmer This is a simple hair trimmer that will suit most men. It has a long battery life, is strong, sturdy, and extremely smooth, contributing to a salon-quality shave. Clean, smooth shaving is made possible by the DuraPower innovation, self-sharpening steel edges, and skin-friendly curved edges. Users can retain a better stable grip thanks to the intuitive structure. This is the best choice if you desire a reliable trimming tool that works swiftly. There is a two-year warranty offered. 2. Wahl Quick Style Trimmer This beard trimmer boasts a sleek appearance and creative functions perfect for the modern man. It has beard, nose, and ear hair trimming heads that can be swapped out. It's one of the best beard trimmers in its price range, with quick charging and good performance. Energiser AAA Lithium-ion Ultimate Battery Washable. This trimmer may be used in the shower thanks to the water-resistant attachments. The operation is cordless. A two-year warranty is included. 3. Bombay Shaving Company Beard Trimmer This cordless trimmer has up to 20 length options and will be your everyday grooming partner. Its comfortable grip and low pricing ensure that you receive a clean cut without burning a hole in your budget. It has the advantage of being able to charge in a flash. It has a 1.5-hour charge time and an 80-minute run duration. Blades made of non-rusting stainless steel last a long time. The sleek and compact form allows for simple movement. Adjustable combs aid in beard taming. The excellent finesse comes from a secure lock. 4. Philips BT3211/15 Beard Trimmer The Philips BT3211/15 has Philips' Lift and Trim technology, which promises a 30 percent faster shave. It is one of the finest trimmers for men because it can be operated with or without a cord. You can anticipate a performance of 60 minutes while using it in wireless mode following recharging it for 1.5 hours. Each of the 20 different length variations for the Philips BT3211/15 has a 0.5-mm difference. The trimmer can effortlessly trim your hair, beard, and body with various length options. The Philips BT3211/15 includes a detachable head, making it simple to clean the self-sharpening stainless steel blades. 5. Braun MGK3221 Trimmer The Braun MGK3221 All-in-One Trimmer is a product that anyone may use. It has a total of 25 accuracy settings in 0.5 increments, so it can be customized to fit any style. This Braun product's versatility is one of its most important features. You can carry them wherever and function without a cord because they run on batteries. Stainless steel razors provide sharpness and longevity. This trimmer's general design makes it easy to operate. 6. Panasonic ER307 Trimmer In India, the Panasonic ER307 is one of the more expensive models. However, this beard/hair trimmer features more than make up for the price. It achieves precision cutting by using high-performance blades that can be washed. There are 12 trim choices available, ranging from 0.2 to 1.8cm. A quick-adjust dial is also included for simple length adjustment. The Panasonic ER307 beard trimmer costs Rs 2,095 in India and is available online and in-store. 7. Xiaomi's Mi Beard Trimmer The Chinese company Xiaomi accompanied its delightful surprise Mi Beard Trimmer, which fared brilliantly in the Indian markets, with the Beard Trimmer 2 in September. Xiaomi has practically improved on every significant feature of the original Mi Beard Trimmer with the new model. A front-facing LED display has been added and supports USB Type-C fast charging. This beard trimmer is packed with features, including 40-length options, stainless steel blades, and a travel lock. It features a battery that lasts 90 minutes in cordless mode, and a 5-minute charge offers you 12 minutes of use, which is 2 minutes longer than the previous model. There is also an IPX7 rating. 8. Ustraa Chrome Beard Trimmer Thanks to indigenous products like Ustraa, grooming is now more widely marketed in the country than ever before. Because of its classy look and vast list of features, the Ustraa Chrome Beard Trimmer has recently been all the rage among guys. The trimmer provides varied trimming with three combs of different diameters (1mm, 3mm, and 5mm). This trimmer's combs are composed of ABS plastic and have a reliable comb locking mechanism. The blades have a titanium coating and, according to Ustraa, sharpen themselves while in use, ensuring precise cutting every time. 9. Havells BT9010 Trimmer Havells promotes its product using the same phrase that Ustraa does: long battery life. Most trimmers employ a proprietary recharging system, whereas Havells employs a micro USB connector. Functionally speaking, this tool's head is broader than other shavers, enabling it to reach a bigger area during trimming effectively. The titanium blades on the Havells Trimmer allow for a total of 20 length settings. 10. Beardo's Multipurpose Trimmer Beardo's Multipurpose Trimmer Kit (PR3058) includes four attachments, two guide combs, and a storage dock. The trimmer features a 5-length facial hair shaver and 20 different length settings. It is composed of stainless steel. It may be operated as a wireless gadget for 50 minutes after 60 minutes of recharging. The length adjustability varies between 1mm to 20mm, and the blades' self-sharpen resembles Ustraa. The trimmer's body is washable, and the shaver head is portable. The battery state is indicated by a built-in LED indicator, which is standard in this market. 11. Realme Beard Trimmer The Realme Beard Trimmer is the most recent addition to India's burgeoning lifestyle industry. With features including a 120-minute runtime, a washable design, and low-noise operation, it's easy to understand why this beard trimmer has quickly garnered appeal. Realme Beard Trimmer has a 4.1-star rating on Flipkart and many people seem to like its style and versatility. 12. DIZO Beard Trimmer Realme's first Techlife ecosystem brand, DIZO, has launched a new product, the Beard Trimmer Plus. The DIZO Beard Trimmer Plus gets a lot right, with 40 length options and 0.5mm precision, and 120-minute battery runtime. Stainless steel blades, an IPX7 rating, low noise operation, and a travel lock are all included in the feature set. Compared to the other models on this list, it's also reasonably priced. DIZO Beard Trimmer Plus has a retail price of Rs 2,295. 13. Misfit by boAt With its own grooming line called Misfit, boAt, India's audio darling, has delved into the lifestyle arena. Since its beginning, boAt has sought to be a lifestyle brand and has established a strong presence in the country with its audio line. The company does not want to limit itself to its acoustic roots now that it has received new investments. With its personal grooming line, it is now poised to take on Xiaomi, Philips, and others. The Misfit T200 G